description.p:
This change changes the default behaviour if NO 
@SupportedSourceVersion
annotation is present on subclass. From 8.40, the Processor will report 
@SourceVersion.latest().

change.compatibility:
First broken, later restored binary compatibility in trunk and
boston. Any outside code calling them as public will break;
however such code is definitely erroneous and should be rewritten.

Code that used Repository as cookie should be changed to:

    ic = (InstanceCookie)node.getCookie(InstanceCookie.class);
    if (ic != null && Repository.class.isAssignableFrom(ic.instanceCookie())) {
    // do stuff
    }
